title: Rock Paper Scissors In Python
description:
This is going to be a tutorial for absolute beginners and will help them in creating their first Game.

Here is the Code

import random 

#Title
print("ROCK PAPER SCISSOR\n")

#Mainloop
while True:
 #Game Variables
 choices = ["Rock", "Paper", "Scissor"]

 score = 0
 print(score)

 guess = input("Enter Your Guess: ")
 print("You Guessed " + guess)

 computer_guess = random.choice(choices)
 print("The Computer Guessed: " + computer_guess)

 #Possibilites
 if guess in choices:
  if guess == computer_guess:
   print("Draw")

  if guess == "Rock" and computer_guess == "Scissor":
   print("You Win Yay!!!")
   score += 1 
   print("Your Score is " + score)

  if guess == "Rock" and computer_guess == "Paper":
   print("Computer Wins")
   print("You Lose")

  if guess == "Paper" and computer_guess == "Rock":
   print("You Win Yay!!!")
   score += 1
   print("Your Score is " + score)

  if guess == "Paper" and computer_guess == "Scissor":
   print("Computer Wins")
   print("You Lose")

  if guess == "Scissor" and computer_guess == "Paper":
   print("You Win Yay!!!")
   score += 1
   print("Your Score is " + score)

  if guess == "Scissor" and computer_guess == "Rock":
   print("Computer Wins")
   print("You Lose")

title: Turtle Race Game
description:
Here is the code for the game

import turtle
import time
from turtle import Turtle
from random import randint

#Creating the main window
window = turtle.Screen()
window.title("Turtle Race Game Tutorial")
window.bgcolor("forestgreen")
turtle.color("white")
turtle.speed(0)
turtle.penup()
turtle.setpos(-140,200)
turtle.write("TURTLE RACE", font=("Arial", 30, "bold"))
turtle.penup()

#Making the dirt
turtle.setpos(-400,-180)
turtle.color("chocolate")
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.pendown()
turtle.forward(800)
turtle.right(90)
turtle.forward(300)
turtle.right(90)
turtle.forward(800)
turtle.right(90)
turtle.forward(300)
turtle.end_fill()

#Finish Line

#FINISH LINE

stamp_size=20
square_size=15
finish_line=200


turtle.color("black")
turtle.shape("square")
turtle.shapesize(square_size/stamp_size)
turtle.penup()

for i in range(10):
    turtle.setpos(finish_line,(150-(i * square_size * 2)))
    turtle.stamp()


for j in range(10):
    turtle.setpos(finish_line + square_size,((150 - square_size)-(j * square_size * 2)))
    turtle.stamp()

turtle.hideturtle()

#Making the first player

turtle1 = Turtle()
turtle1.speed(0)
turtle1.color("black")
turtle1.penup()
turtle1.shape("turtle")
turtle1.goto(-250,100)
turtle1.pendown()

#Making the second player

turtle2 = Turtle()
turtle2.speed(0)
turtle2.color("red")
turtle2.penup()
turtle2.shape("turtle")
turtle2.goto(-250,50)
turtle2.pendown()

#Making the third player

turtle3 = Turtle()
turtle3.speed(0)
turtle3.color("yellow")
turtle3.penup()
turtle3.shape("turtle")
turtle3.goto(-250,0)
turtle3.pendown()

#Making the fourth player

turtle4 = Turtle()
turtle4.speed(0)
turtle4.color("magenta")
turtle4.penup()
turtle4.shape("turtle")
turtle4.goto(-250,-50)
turtle4.pendown()

time.sleep(1)#Pause the game for a second

for i in range(145):
    turtle1.forward(randint(1, 5))
    turtle2.forward(randint(1, 5))
    turtle3.forward(randint(1, 5))
    turtle4.forward(randint(1, 5))

turtle.hideturtle()

window.mainloop()

Hope you all like the video :)
